<div class='headBanner'>
    <div class='full_page'>
      <div class='half_page category'>
        <h3>Purpose of this Site</h3>
        <hr />
      </div>
      <div class='category aboutCodiki'>
          <div class='full_page' id='aboutArticle'>
                <h2>Why Contribute?</h2>
                <p>If you're stuck in one an idea or find yourself in a work rut, it can be tough to advance. After all, how do you learn new skills and make yourself a more desirable hire if there's no way for you to practice your skills? Codid has lists of projects contributed by the community that you can use during your free time, this can help add to your resumes but also to pick up the knowledge and experience that will help them move on to bigger and better positions at your current companies or somewhere else altogether.</p>
                <h2>How to Contribute?</h2>
                <p>To contribute ideas, simply register for a accout. Check out what categories/topics we already have. If it is not there, create one (no one is stopping you). Then simply add an article to a category and your done. Simply as that. </p>
                <% if current_contributor %>
                    <p><small> |</small><%= link_to 'Create New Category', new_category_path %> </p>
                    <p><small> |</small><%= link_to 'Create New Article', new_article_path %></p>
                <% end %>
              <h2>Why Register?</h2>
              <p>Diversity is great and enriches life on many levels, but, particularly when it comes to things like programming. Didn't you have ideas that you thought would be great to see what others come up with? It can be truly rewarding to say you contributed to a community to help others like you become better.</p>
              <p><small> |</small><%= link_to 'Click here to Register for an Accout', new_contributor_path %></p>
          </div>
      </div>
    </div>
</div>
